title: $A surges against lower $US
text:
Wed, Jul 22, 2015, 7:09 AM AEST - Australia Markets open in 2 hrs 51 mins $A surges against lower $US AAP – 28 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is higher after the greenback fell by one per cent in overnight trade. 
At 0630 AEST on Wednesday, the local currency was trading at 74.25 US cents, up from 73.58 cents on Tuesday. 
The Aussie surged against the US dollar, despite a lack of market moving data with traders selling the greenback to take profit. 
CURRENCY SNAPSHOT AT 0630 AEST ON WEDNESDAY 
One Australian dollar buys: 
* 74.25 US cents, from 73.58 cents on Tuesday 
* 92.00 Japanese yen, from 91.53 yen 
* 67.85 euro cents, from 67.94 euro cents 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session)
